dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-durability-fsync-policy.md:5:desc: SQLite synchronous mode + WAL checkpoint policy + durability/recovery numerical targets
dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-durability-fsync-policy.md:23:- **WAL `journal_mode=WAL`** + engine-managed `wal_autocheckpoint` (specific value lives in `design/engine.md`; not zero, not unbounded). Already mandatory per ADR-0.6.0-single-writer-thread.
dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-durability-fsync-policy.md:24:- **Durability target.** Zero corruption on power-cut. Up to 100ms of final-commit loss on power-cut acceptable. Zero commit loss on OS-crash (fsync at checkpoint).
dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-durability-fsync-policy.md:29:**A — `synchronous=NORMAL` + default checkpointing (chosen).** Industry-standard SQLite production posture. Survives OS-crash without loss; may lose final ~100ms on power-cut but never corrupts. Modest fsync cost.
dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-durability-fsync-policy.md:31:**B — `synchronous=FULL` + smaller checkpoint window.** Per-commit fsync; survives power-cut with zero loss. Write latency 5–10× higher per commit. Strongest durability; not justified by any 0.6.0 forcing function.
dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-durability-fsync-policy.md:37:- `design/engine.md` documents the PRAGMA set + `wal_autocheckpoint` value.
