dev/roadmap/0.8.3.md:5:status: direction (REDIRECTED 2026-06-19 by the M1 NO-GO — 0.8.3 was "M2 full multi-hop graph study"; now retargeted to index-key enrichment + passage-dense retrieval, the non-graph levers M1 pointed at. EXTENDED 2026-06-21 by the capability-status-report review — ADJ-6..10: embedder-ceiling probe, D2 content harness-proxy gate, D0 agentic-memory measurement-unblock, latency-regression gate, both-null fallback. The measurement + prerequisite work in ADJ-6..10 is HITL-APPROVED; engine promotions stay behind the Slice-0 gate.)
dev/roadmap/0.8.3.md:6:desc: After the 0.8.2 M1 DECISIVE NO-GO on the multi-hop graph arm (n=300; ΔF1 −0.0405, CI upper +0.031 < +0.04 materiality), 0.8.3 redirects AWAY from graph-traversal retrieval and toward the non-graph levers M1 surfaced: (1) index-key enrichment (revived 0.8.1 R6 — extracted facts appended to a doc's OWN FTS content, placebo-confirmed +0.075 content value) and (2) passage-dense retrieval (the single strongest M1 arm, 0.487 > fused 0.450). The former M2 graph-multi-hop study (2Wiki/MultiHop-RAG/IRCoT-on-graph) is DROPPED — graph multi-hop is refuted on both recall (0.8.1 n=40) and answer-accuracy (0.8.2 n=300). The 2026-06-21 capability-report review adds three $0 measurement gates that de-risk the two engine builds before they are committed (embedder ceiling, D2 content-at-scale) and a first-class measurement-unblock track (D0) so the product's defining number — end-to-end agentic-memory accuracy vs Mem0/Zep — becomes producible within 0.8.3.
