dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:30:- **Checkpoint cost.** Under WAL, writes append to `-wal`; checkpoints fold it
dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:31:  back into the main DB. `wal_autocheckpoint` (default ~1000 pages) triggers
dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:32:  periodic checkpoints *on the writer* — a bursty cost like FTS5 merges. Capture
dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:33:  the spikes (`on_slow_statement`) and the `PRAGMA wal_checkpoint` frame counts
dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:34:  (`TruncateWalReport` shape: `busy`, `log_frames`, `checkpointed_frames`).
dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:36:  WAL fsyncs only at checkpoint. For small batches this dominates writer latency
dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:38:- **WAL growth** — a long ingest without checkpoint grows `-wal`; reads then scan
dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:47:- **Snapshot vs checkpoint contention** — a reader's DEFERRED snapshot taken
dev/profiling/11-sqlite-pragmas.md:48:  while a checkpoint runs can pay extra. Note if a checkpoint fired mid-run.
