     1	"""0.8.3 D0b — per-class FathomDB − {Mem0, Graphiti/Zep, naive-RAG} parity runner.
     2	
     3	THE TARGET (design `0.8.3-mem0-parity.md` §2/§4): per memory class, the external
     4	``FathomDB − {mem0_oss, graphiti_zep, naive_rag}`` delta on **(a) strict full-gold
     5	Recall@K (LLM-free, $0)** and **(b) identical-answerer accuracy (PRICED)**, each with
     6	a paired 95% CI + a per-class paired MDE, on the re-pinned power-sized gold
     7	(``repin_hash 2916cace``). The accuracy deltas feed the frozen
     8	:func:`eval.decision_rule_083.decide_083` → REACHED / NOT_REACHED + per-class gap.
     9	
    10	Resilience ([[priced-runs-need-resilience-before-spend]]) — REUSES
    11	``m1_verdict_run``'s proven mechanisms, never a hand-rolled weaker one:
    12	
    13	* :func:`eval.m1_verdict_run._atomic_write_json` — temp-file + ``os.replace`` atomic
    14	  checkpoint; a kill mid-write can never corrupt the live sidecar.
    15	* :func:`eval.m1_verdict_run._resolve_resume` — auto-resume ON BY DEFAULT from the
    16	  ``<output>.checkpoint.json`` sidecar; a relaunch reuses every persisted ``(qid,arm)``
    17	  answer cell (key-present incl. ``None`` = a real abstention, reused; absent = a prior
    18	  failure, re-called) → zero re-spend.
    19	* The answerer is :class:`eval.m1_baseline_run.CostTrackingAnswerer` — exponential
    20	  backoff over transient 429/5xx; a cell fails only after ``max_retries`` are exhausted.
    21	* **failure ≠ abstention**: a retry-exhausted cell is MISSING (absent key), counted in
    22	  ``n_errors``, never persisted as a scored ``None`` (which would deflate the arm).
    23	* **completeness validity guard**: a pass is citable only at completeness ≥
    24	  :data:`VALID_COMPLETENESS_FLOOR`; below it the run is flagged INVALID.
    25	
    26	The only priced seam is the shared answerer (the R2 identical-answerer invariant);
    27	retrieval / recall / scoring / bootstrap is $0. Pure helpers (``paired_*`` /
    28	``class_delta`` / ``per_class_delta_table`` / ``external_per_class_for_decide`` /
    29	``answer_completeness``) are import-light + backend-free so the unit tests run with
    30	fake adapters + a fake answerer (no DB, no LLM, no ``mem0``).
    31	"""
