   140	**gated product metric**, a retrieval recall number alone cannot prove "as-good-or-better than
   141	Mem0/Zep." The end-to-end eval is the only honest way to make that comparison — because the peer
   142	systems (Mem0, Zep) report end-to-end answer accuracy, not first-stage recall, and the comparison
   143	must be **on a fair basis with an identical answerer**.
   144	
   145	### 3.2 Identical-answerer constraint (the load-bearing design rule)
   146	
   147	The **same LLM / same prompt / same context-window** is used as the answerer for all three
   148	systems — FathomDB, Mem0-OSS, and naive-RAG. **Only the retrieval+memory layer differs.** This
   149	isolates the retrieval signal from the model signal. Any comparison that uses different answerers
   150	or different prompts for different systems is NOT R2.
   151	
   152	This constraint is non-negotiable:
   153	- Vendor-reported parity claims (e.g. Mem0 92.5% self-reported, Zep 63.8% vs Mem0 49.0% in the
   154	  LoCoMo dispute) use different answerers, prompts, and context compositions — they are **not
   155	  comparable** to a Recall@K number and **not acceptable** as a baseline. Only R2 (same answerer)
   156	  can produce a fair comparison.
   157	- Any HITL parity claim after Slice 25 **MUST cite R2 numbers**, never vendor self-reported numbers.
   158	
   159	### 3.3 Baselines
   160	
   161	- **Mem0-OSS**: the local open-source Mem0 library (`pip install mem0ai`, NOT the Mem0 cloud API;
   162	  the cloud API would violate the no-API footprint requirement for the eval baseline). Use the
   163	  same local corpus.
   164	- **Naive-RAG baseline**: flat retrieval (BM25 or dense, no memory graph/update logic) over the
   165	  same documents.
   166	
   167	Both baselines use the **identical answerer** (same LLM, same prompt, same context-window).
   168	
   169	### 3.4 Per-class scoring
   170	
   171	Score results stratified by query class. At minimum:
   172	
   173	| Class | What it tests |
   174	|-------|--------------|
   175	| `factoid` | Specific retrievable fact (number, name, date) |
   176	| `temporal` | Time-aware questions ("what did we know in March") |
   177	| `multi_hop` | Questions requiring 2+ connected facts |
   178	| `knowledge_update` | Questions about facts that have changed / been superseded |
   179	| `multi_session` | Questions spanning multiple conversation sessions |
   180	
   181	**Abstention counts against recall.** If the system returns no answer when one exists, it is a
   182	miss. If the system returns an answer when no answer exists (the negative class), it is a false
   183	positive. Both are scored.
   184	
   185	### 3.5 Metric
   186	
   187	- **Per-class Evidence Recall@K** (from `dev/design/ir-recall-measure.md`) — the primary metric
   188	- **Per-class answerer accuracy** — the end-to-end score (retrieval + answerer joint accuracy)
   189	- **Abstention rate** per class — separately reported
   190	
   191	AC-077 (Evidence Recall@K, strict all-of) is the **product gate** and is measured directly.
   192	The per-class answerer accuracy is the **north-star** comparison metric for Mem0/Zep parity.
   193	
   194	### 3.6 Footprint
   195	
   196	- The **answerer/baseline LLM** is **test-infra** (BYO/local) — it is not a FathomDB product
   197	  dependency; it is gated behind a feature flag or environment variable (like the embedder tests)
   198	- The **engine SUT** (FathomDB) stays **no-API** throughout the eval; the eval harness does not
   199	  enable any network call from FathomDB itself
   200	- **Local Mem0-OSS** (not cloud API) is mandatory; cloud Mem0 is a footprint violation for the
   201	  eval infrastructure
   202	
   203	### 3.7 What Slice 25 delivers
   204	
   205	- A **runnable R2 eval harness** (Python) implementing the identical-answerer protocol
   206	- A **local Mem0-OSS adapter** (wraps the OSS library with the same interface as FathomDB)
   207	- A **naive-RAG adapter** as the floor baseline
   208	- A **results document** (`dev/plans/runs/IR-C-r2-eval-results.md` or equivalent) with actual
   209	  per-class numbers for all three systems, including the N (queries), the answerer/version, and
   210	  the corpus snapshot hash
   211	- **DOC-INDEX** updated with the harness and results
   212	
   213	### 3.8 Falsifiable bar
   214	
   215	Slice 25 commits the R2 harness + baseline adapter + a results doc with actual per-class numbers.
   216	Any HITL review can verify:
   217	
   218	1. The identical-answerer constraint (same LLM, same prompt, cited in the results doc)
   219	2. The local-Mem0-OSS condition (not the cloud API)
   220	3. Per-class breakdown present for all 5 classes
   221	4. Abstention reporting present
   222	5. Corpus hash matches `fe973fcd…`
   223	
   224	---
   225	
   226	## 4. Decision ①: AC-077 gate vs R2 north-star
   227	
   228	| Dimension | AC-077 (Evidence Recall@K) | R2 (end-to-end parity eval) |
   229	|-----------|---------------------------|-----------------------------|
   230	| Role | **Product gate** (GATED) | **Report-only north-star** |

